ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.203                Enzyme
NAME        UDP-N-acetylbacillosamine N-acetyltransferase;
            UDP-4-amino-4,6-dideoxy-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine N-acetyltransferase;
            pglD (gene name)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     acetyl-CoA:UDP-4-amino-4,6-dideoxy-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine N-acetyltransferase
REACTION    acetyl-CoA + UDP-N-acetylbacillosamine = CoA + UDP-N,N'-diacetylbacillosamine [RN:R10099]
ALL_REAC    R10099
SUBSTRATE   acetyl-CoA [CPD:C00024];
            UDP-N-acetylbacillosamine [CPD:C04630]
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            UDP-N,N'-diacetylbacillosamine [CPD:C20357]
COMMENT     The product, UDP-N,N'-diacetylbacillosamine, is an intermediate in protein glycosylation pathways in several bacterial species, including N-linked glycosylation of certain L-asparagine residues in Campylobacter species [1,2] and O-linked glycosylation of certain L-serine residues in Neisseria species [3].
